{"article_id":"DDmjleJnfjlfTUR0","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"FBI Warns Of 'Grave Concerns ' About 'Accuracy ' Of GOP Snooping Memo","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"The FBI clashed with the White House on Wednesday over the much discussed Republican memo","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"that alleges","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"the bureau abused its surveillance powers .","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"The bureau said","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"it has `` grave concerns '' about the `` accuracy '' of the document","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"that the president supports making public .","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"Meanwhile , the ranking Democrat on the House intelligence committee ,","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"which voted to release the memo ,","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"says","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"Republicans secretly made `` material changes '' to the document after the decision","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"to make it public .","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"The FBI issued a rare , two-paragraph statement","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"undercutting the position","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"taken by President Trump and his top aides","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"that the memo should be disclosed to the public soon .","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"`` With regard to the House Intelligence Committee 's memorandum ,","depth":11},{"id":17,"text":"the FBI was provided a limited opportunity","depth":13},{"id":18,"text":"to review this memo the day","depth":14},{"id":19,"text":"before the committee voted to release it , ''","depth":14},{"id":20,"text":"the FBI said .","depth":12},{"id":21,"text":"`` As expressed during our initial review ,","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"we have grave concerns about material omissions of fact","depth":12},{"id":23,"text":"that fundamentally impact the memo 's accuracy . ''","depth":12},{"id":24,"text":"The FBI statement appeared amid a bitter political fight over the memo ,","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"which was drawn up by committee Chairman Devin Nunes of California and the panel 's Republican staff .","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"Nunes and other GOP allies of Trump say","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"the memo makes the case about an epic scandal inside federal law enforcement .","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"The Justice Department has already said","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"that releasing the memo would be `` extraordinarily reckless ''","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"and could hurt national security or ongoing investigations .","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"Nunes , a Trump ally","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"who served on the president 's transition team ,","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"responded to the FBI with a fiery statement of his own .","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"`` Having stonewalled Congress ' demands for information for nearly a year ,","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"it 's no surprise to see the FBI and DOJ issue spurious objections","depth":11},{"id":36,"text":"to allowing the American people to see information","depth":12},{"id":37,"text":"related to surveillance abuses at these agencies , ''","depth":12},{"id":38,"text":"he said ,","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"referring to the Department of Justice .","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"Nunes accused the FBI of leaving out important information in its presentations to Congress and the courts .","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"And he invited the bureau to make public all the information","depth":12},{"id":42,"text":"it has on `` these abuses . '' `` It 's clear that top officials used unverified information in a court document","depth":12},{"id":43,"text":"to fuel a counter-intelligence investigation during an American political campaign , ''","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"Nunes said .","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"`` Once the truth gets out ,","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"we can begin taking steps","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"to ensure","depth":12},{"id":48,"text":"our intelligence agencies and courts are never misused like this again . ''","depth":12},{"id":49,"text":"Democrats say","depth":6},{"id":50,"text":"the four-page document is misleading and part of an effort","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"to undermine the bureau and Justice Department special counsel Robert Mueller .","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"His office is investigating possible coordination between the Trump campaign and Russia 's attack on the 2016 election .","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"The committee 's top Democrat , Adam Schiff , sent a letter Wednesday to Nunes","depth":5},{"id":54,"text":"charging","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"that `` material changes '' had been made to the memo","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"after it was voted on","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"and that the version","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"handed over to the White House","depth":12},{"id":59,"text":"`` is not , in fact , the same document . '' `` Upon our discovery","depth":12},{"id":60,"text":"that the document","depth":14},{"id":61,"text":"sent for public review","depth":14},{"id":62,"text":"had been secretly altered ,","depth":13},{"id":63,"text":"the Majority belatedly afforded the Minority an opportunity this evening","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"to compare the document","depth":13},{"id":65,"text":"transmitted on Monday night by the Majority to the White House","depth":13},{"id":66,"text":"with the document","depth":13},{"id":67,"text":"made available to all House Members since January 18 , ''","depth":13},{"id":68,"text":"Schiff wrote .","depth":8},{"id":69,"text":"`` After reviewing both versions ,","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"it is clear that the Majority made material changes to the version","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"it sent to the White House ,","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"which Committee Members were never apprised of ,","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"never had the opportunity","depth":12},{"id":74,"text":"to review ,","depth":12},{"id":75,"text":"and never approved , ''","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"he added ,","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"calling the alleged alterations `` deeply troubling . ''","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"Republicans responded to the letter ,","depth":6},{"id":79,"text":"saying","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"Schiff 's complaints were merely a `` strange attempt","depth":11},{"id":81,"text":"to thwart publication of the memo . '' Democrats were `` complaining about minor edits to the memo ,","depth":11},{"id":82,"text":"including grammatical fixes and two edits","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"requested by the F.B.I . and by [ Democrats ] themselves , ''","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"Jack Langer , a spokesman for Nunes , said in a statement ,","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"according to The New York Times .","depth":7},{"id":86,"text":"In a Washington Post op-ed , Schiff noted","depth":6},{"id":87,"text":"that the memo also paves the way for the possible firing of Mueller or the man","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"overseeing the probe ,","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"Deputy Attorney General Rod Rosenstein .","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"That would allow the White House to replace Rosenstein with someone","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"willing to shut down the investigation .","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"The intelligence committee voted along party lines on Monday to release the memo to the public .","depth":6},{"id":93,"text":"The White House says","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"it is currently reviewing the document ,","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"and the president said Tuesday night","depth":8},{"id":96,"text":"that the chances","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"of its being released","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"are `` 100 percent . ''","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"For now , the memo remains classified .","depth":5},{"id":100,"text":"Lawmakers","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"who have read it","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"say","depth":8},{"id":103,"text":"it alleges","depth":8},{"id":104,"text":"the FBI and Justice Department gave scurrilous or incomplete evidence to the Foreign Intelligence Surveillance Court","depth":9},{"id":105,"text":"in order to surveil people in the Trump camp .","depth":9},{"id":106,"text":"In its statement , the FBI says","depth":8},{"id":107,"text":"it `` takes seriously '' its obligations to the FISA court","depth":9},{"id":108,"text":"that approves surveillance for foreign intelligence purposes .","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"The bureau says","depth":8},{"id":110,"text":"it is `` committed to working with the appropriate oversight entities","depth":9},{"id":111,"text":"to ensure the continuing integrity of the FISA process . ''","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"Current and former intelligence officials have expressed concern","depth":6},{"id":113,"text":"that the FBI would be unable to counter any factual errors or misrepresentations in the memo","depth":7},{"id":114,"text":"because the information","depth":9},{"id":115,"text":"it is based on","depth":9},{"id":116,"text":"remains classified .","depth":8},{"id":117,"text":"The statements from the FBI and Nunes followed accusations by a Democrat on the intelligence committee","depth":6},{"id":118,"text":"that Nunes worked with the White House","depth":7},{"id":119,"text":"to prepare and now release the memo .","depth":7},{"id":120,"text":"On CNN Wednesday , Rep. Mike Quigley , D-Ill. , relayed a conversation","depth":9},{"id":121,"text":"he said","depth":10},{"id":122,"text":"he had with Nunes during a committee meeting .","depth":10},{"id":123,"text":"`` I asked the chairman ,","depth":12},{"id":124,"text":"'Did he work with ' [ the Trump administration ] ,","depth":12},{"id":125,"text":"and I asked all the preliminaries","depth":13},{"id":126,"text":"- coordinate , discuss -","depth":13},{"id":127,"text":"and he said ,","depth":13},{"id":128,"text":"'not to my knowledge , ' ``","depth":13},{"id":129,"text":"Quigley said .","depth":10},{"id":130,"text":"`` And I asked him ,","depth":11},{"id":131,"text":"'Did your staff ? '","depth":11},{"id":132,"text":"And then he became quite agitated","depth":11},{"id":133,"text":"and he said ,","depth":12},{"id":134,"text":"' I 'm not answering that . ' ``","depth":12},{"id":135,"text":"Quigley said","depth":10},{"id":136,"text":"there was precedent","depth":11},{"id":137,"text":"for questioning Nunes ' contacts with the White House .","depth":11},{"id":138,"text":"He pointed to what he called the Republican chairman 's `` midnight ride '' to the White House in March","depth":10},{"id":139,"text":"to receive classified documents from the administration","depth":11},{"id":140,"text":"alleging improper `` unmasking '' of Trump associates in intelligence reports .","depth":11},{"id":141,"text":"`` I fully believe","depth":12},{"id":142,"text":"that Chairman Nunes has not changed his tactics .","depth":12},{"id":143,"text":"He began this investigation as a subsidiary of the White House , as someone","depth":12},{"id":144,"text":"who was coordinating with them","depth":13},{"id":145,"text":"rather than being an independent investigator , ''","depth":13},{"id":146,"text":"Quigley said .","depth":10},{"id":147,"text":"`` The sad part is he is the chairman of the committee","depth":10},{"id":148,"text":"that is investigating the most important attack on our country 's democracy in our lifetime . ''","depth":10},{"id":149,"text":"Nunes ' office did not immediately respond to a request for comment .","depth":6},{"id":150,"text":"As Democrats raised questions about a possible White House role","depth":8},{"id":151,"text":"in crafting the memo ,","depth":8},{"id":152,"text":"White House chief of staff John Kelly said","depth":9},{"id":153,"text":"he expected the memo to be made public soon .","depth":9},{"id":154,"text":"`` It will be released here pretty quick ,","depth":11},{"id":155,"text":"I think ,","depth":11},{"id":156,"text":"and then the whole world can see it , ''","depth":10},{"id":157,"text":"Kelly told Fox News Radio on Wednesday .","depth":9},{"id":158,"text":"Although the White House 's preference","depth":10},{"id":159,"text":"for making the memo public","depth":10},{"id":160,"text":"is clear ,","depth":9},{"id":161,"text":"it remains unclear , at this point , exactly how the document would be released .","depth":8},{"id":162,"text":"A senior Republican on the intelligence committee , Rep. Michael Conaway of Texas , told NPR","depth":9},{"id":163,"text":"that the memo would be published in the Congressional Record .","depth":9},{"id":164,"text":"`` As I understand the mechanics ,","depth":11},{"id":165,"text":"the way","depth":13},{"id":166,"text":"we actually release","depth":13},{"id":167,"text":"is that we insert it in the Congressional Record .","depth":12},{"id":168,"text":"The House has to be in session","depth":11},{"id":169,"text":"to do that , ''","depth":11},{"id":170,"text":"he said .","depth":9},{"id":171,"text":"The House is currently out of session .","depth":6},{"id":172,"text":"It 's scheduled to return for a pro forma session Friday afternoon ,","depth":7},{"id":173,"text":"so","depth":8},{"id":174,"text":"if Conaway is right ,","depth":9},{"id":175,"text":"then late Friday is the earliest","depth":10},{"id":176,"text":"the memo could be officially released .","depth":10}],"relations":[{"parent":353,"left":0,"right":352,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":352,"left":267,"right":351,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":267,"left":228,"right":266,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":228,"left":187,"right":227,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":187,"left":182,"right":186,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":182,"left":179,"right":181,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":179,"left":1,"right":178,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":178,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":181,"left":4,"right":180,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":180,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":186,"left":184,"right":1